article.headline: Siena 58, Fairfield 47
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Three Siena players scored in double figures Tuesday in a 58-47 victory over Fairfield in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference play. Kenny Hasbrouck led Siena (11-11, 6-8) with 15 points, while Antoine Jordan had 14 and David Ryan scored 10. Siena led 24-19 at the half. Fairfield (8-14, 6-8) was led by Danny Oglesby with 14 points and Jonathan Han with 10. Siena took its largest lead, 13 points, with 1:19 left in the game.
